reviews.text: As I never travel north, I specifically asked the women in the ticket counter if my ticket was valid on the next train. Showed her my ticket and she said yes. Get on the train and apparently it's only valid on hull trains. God awful experience and it's cost me £80. More than my original RETURN ticket would have. Train your staff and have them take time to provide useful advice.
Awesome Staff.. passion and a lot of help if you need it.. thanks guys... you all deserve at least a bonus ..going beyond the call of duty.

Terrie with an “ie” was very inconvenienced when I was unable to use the automated machine in the lobby. She was rude and ignorant. The fact that she had to press some buttons to print my ticked almost caused her to have a stroke. Get well soon Terrie with an “ie” 🤨

on 24th March,my  friend and I arrived at 8.30 am at Retford station to catch the Sunday morning train to London. Usually a lovely experience at the station but the blonde lady in the ticket office was incredibly misera i.e.. We needed to pay for parking but she was rude  offhand and we felt like apologising for bothering her and getting her up from her precious seat.  what a shame when everyone else is pleasant.
The higher level of the station is impressive what with a curve each side of the station making for good rail photography, the letdown is the lack of service and information on the lower level.
